description:
Job responsibilities:-

- Provide full range of secretarial and administrative support to Chairman;
- Manage calendars, meeting schedules, personal & family affairs including director's quarter maintenance, maids and drivers management, administrative support to the relatives of Chairman;
- Maintain filling system and confidential information in a professional manner;
- Closely liaise and coordinate with internal and external parties to ensure smooth business operations.

Jobs requirements:-

- Degree holder with 3 years solid experience;
- Excellent command in spoken and written English, Cantonese and Mandarin;
- Proficient PC knowledge in MS Word and Excel;
- Multi-tasking, well-organized, detail-minded with strong communication and interpersonal skills;
- Immediately available is highly preferred.

We are a well-established property leasing, management and investment company located in Wanchai-Admiralty area, now inviting an experienced candidate for the position of Executive Assistant (Trainee) / Management Associate.

Responsibilities:

Assist Senior Management by providing administrative and co-ordination support in the various areas of business duties;
Draft English and Chinese correspondences, emails, memos, letters, presentation materials and reports;
Coordinate meetings, prepare agenda and minutes;
Assist in coordination of daily tasks and liaise with internal and external parties;
Support office administrative work when necessary.

Requirements: 

Degree holder in any disciplines with at least 2 years’ working experience in assisting executive management;
A good team player with strong communication and interpersonal skills;
Owned driving license is an advantage;
Self-motivated and loyal, with strong sense of commitment;
Skills in PC office softwares (English/Chinese);
Proficient in English, Cantonese and Mandarin;
Overseas travelling may be required;
Candidates with less experience will be considered as Executive Assistant Trainee.

We offer an attractive remuneration package and excellent career prospects to the right candidate.  Please send full resume, current and expected salary, contact number and the availability to us for interview.

Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.

The applicant must possess
a recognised degree;
a minimum of 1 year's post-qualification experience;
proactive and customer-oriented;
good sense of responsibility and be a pleasant team player;
proficiency in Cangjie and / or Sucheng input method; and
good command of both written and spoken English and Chinese (including Putonghua).
(Applicants who do not possess the required qualifications and / or experience may be considered for Assistant – Registration Services.)

Duties include
to vet the registration scheme applications in accordance to the Policies and Procedures as well as service pledge;
to provide registration services and application services to other CIC service offerings in CIC Service Centres located at Kowloon Bay and Nam Cheong or other CIC premises;
to perform data entry and data analysis work;
to handle enquiries and complaints according to service pledge;
to maintain the IT System and update the scheme website and publicity materials;
to support events and other administrative duties of the Registration Services; and
to carry out any other duties as assigned from time to time by the Executive Director.

Applications
The position is on a renewable fixed-term contract (subject to performance and operational needs) for a period of 2 years.
Please click the below “Apply Online” to complete the application form and upload the updated curriculum vitae, the results of English and Chinese Language obtained in public examinations, current and expected salary together with a covering letter stating one’s suitability for the job on or before 31 January 2022.
For further details on CIC please refer to website: http://www.cic.hk.

DEPARTMENT OF ELECTRICAL ENGINEERING

Executive Assistant (Ref. 22011404-E)

Duties

The appointee will be required to:

(a) provide administrative support to both academic and research programmes;

(b) support a wide range of activities of the Unit, including administration of student-related matters (e.g. admission, registration, examination, timetabling and student record), and various student-related events and projects;

(c) provide secretarial support to meetings and committees;

(d) compile statistical reports and maintain database;

(e) support general office administration; and

(f) perform any other duties as assigned by the Head of the Unit or his delegates.
The appointee may be required to work outside office hours.

Qualifications

Applicants should have:

(a) a recognized degree or an equivalent qualification;

(b) at least two years of relevant post-qualification experience;

(c) a good command of both English and Chinese, with fluency in Putonghua being an advantage;

(d) proficiency in computer software applications including MS office (e.g. MS Excel, Word, PowerPoint) and Chinese word processing;

(e) good communication, interpersonal and time management skills; and

(f) self-motivation and the ability to work independently and proactively.

Preference will be given to those with experience in tertiary institutions/similar organizations.

Shortlisted candidates may be invited to sit for a written test and a computer test.

Remuneration and Conditions of Service

A highly competitive remuneration package will be offered. Initial appointment will be on a fixed-term one-year gratuity-bearing contract. Re-engagement thereafter is subject to mutual agreement. Applicants should state their current and expected salary in the application.

Application

Please send a completed application form by post to Human Resources Office, 13/F, Li Ka Shing Tower, The Hong Kong Polytechnic University, Hung Hom, Kowloon, Hong Kong or via email by clicking "Apply Now".  Application forms can be downloaded from https://www.polyu.edu.hk/hro/careers/guidelines_and_forms/forms.  If a separate curriculum vitae is to be provided, please still complete the application form which will help speed up the recruitment process.  Consideration of applications will commence on 26 January 2022 until the position is filled.  The University’s Personal Information Collection Statement for recruitment can be found at https://www.polyu.edu.hk/hro/careers/guidelines_and_forms/pics_for_recruitment.

PolyU is an equal opportunity employer committed to diversity and inclusivity.  All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to gender, ethnicity, nationality, family status or physical or mental disabilities.

ROLES & RESPONSIBILITIES:

Responsible for recruitment process including interview and selection, handle employees on-boarding to off-boarding, verification of candidate's qualification and visa application procedures;
Responsible for issuing employment contract and other personnel letters;
Perform payroll functions including monthly payroll, MPF, and filing of tax return;
Liaise with the Government departments to ensure compliance with Employment Ordinance, Inland Revenue Ordinances, etc;
Liaise with different services providers such as broker, insurers and MPF trustee for HR operations;
Support the development and implementation HR policies, procedures and HR system;
To maintain accurate employee record in HR system and filing system;
Responsible for daily HR operations and general staff enquiries; and
Handle ad-hoc projects as assigned.

REQUIREMENTS:

Higher diploma or above in Human Resources Management or related disciplines;
Be well-versed in Employment Ordinance and human resource business functions;
At least 1 year of human resources experience;
Have self-motivation, strong analytical and coordination skills;
Able to handle sensitive information with confidentiality;
Able to work under pressure and finish tasks with tight deadline; and
Possess excellent command written and spoken English and Chinese languages (including Putonghua).

Appointment will initially be made on contract basis for up to two years, renewable subject to performance.

(Ref: AO/EA (REG) 2022-01-14)

Responsibilities:
provide administrative and logistic support on programme development (programme accreditation and reaccreditation), synchronisation and standardisation of programme accreditation documents, meetings and other accreditation matters;
assist in the preparation of programme accreditation documents;
handle and maintain central filing on programme development and programme quality assurance matters; and
serve as secretary to committees and working groups.

Applicants should:
possess a recognised degree, preferably with 2 years of relevant working experience;
be a fast learner, proactive, self-motivated, a good team player and able to work independently with strong sense of responsibility;
possess good interpersonal and communication skills;
have a good command of written and spoken English and Chinese (Cantonese and Putonghua); and
have good PC knowledge including MS Word, Excel and Chinese Processing.
Work experience in the tertiary education sector will be an advantage.  Applicants with less experience will be considered as Executive Assistant.


Salary will be commensurate with qualifications and experience.  Interested applicant should visit this link https://recruit.hsu.edu.hk/ and apply on or before 30 January 2022.  The University reserves the right not to fill the position in this exercise.
Applicants who are not invited to an interview within three months may consider their applications unsuccessful.  All information received will be treated in strict confidence, and the data collected will be used for recruitment purposes only.  The Personal Information Collection Statement will be provided upon request.
The Hang Seng University of Hong Kong, incorporated in Hong Kong with limited liability by guarantee, is an equal opportunity employer.

 Responsibilities:

Provide all-rounded secretarial and administrative support to Senior Management in a professional manner;
Arrange & coordinate calendar management & meetings for senior management;
Assist Management in liaising with internal and external parties for the group's business activities & project management etc.;
Prepare various types of document including presentation materials, management report, minutes and meeting agenda etc.;
Maintain records, filing and handle details of highly confidential matters properly;
Handle incoming and outgoing correspondence and some translations if necessary; and
Perform ad-hoc duties and business travel as assigned by company

Requirements:

Degree holder in law or business related disciplines;
At least 3 years' relevant working experience gained from sizable conglomerate groups or financial groups or serving listing executives;
Candidate with experience working in financial industry or listing firms is a plus;
Strong familiarity and knowledge in communicating and working with Executive Management and Senior Executives
Excellent organizing and planning skills, able to perform multi-tasks to meet tight schedule and attentive to details 
Mature, responsible, trustworthy, flexible;
Excellent command in spoken and written English and Chinese (including Putonghua); and 
Proficient in MS office including Word, Excel, PowerPoint and Chinese Word Processing

Please submit your application to us with your  availability  and  expected salary.

Responsibilities:

Reporting to a Director
Provide full range of good quality secretarial and administrative support;
Manage all business and personal issues for the Director in professional manner, including but not limited to meeting and travel schedules, social events and functions co-ordination etc.;
Prepare business correspondences, presentation materials, compile reports and meeting minutes in a variety of formats independently and professionally;
Liaise with internal and external parties to ensure smooth business operations;
Manage payments, claims and reimbursements;
Handle sensitive and confidential data and documents in professional manner;
Assist in ad-hoc duties as assigned.


Requirements:           

University Graduate or equivalent;
Minimum 8 years’ relevant experience with proven track record in serving senior executives or directors, preferably in sizeable companies;
Ability of maintaining sensitive and confidential information with strictest confidence;
Proficient in MS Office applications with Chinese word processing;
Strong inter-personal and communication skills;
Excellent command of spoken and written English, Cantonese and Mandarin;
Mature, self-motivated, meticulous and able to handle multiple tasks with discretion.

SCHOOL OF COMMUNICATIION AND FILM

Academy of Film

Executive Officer / Executive Assistant (PR0466/21-22)

The appointee is expected to provide secretarial and administrative support to undergraduate programme offered by the Academy of Film.

Duties:
assisting in the day-to-day operation, including programme promotion and development, student recruitment and admissions, student record update, course and examination scheduling, and organisation of events and activities such as workshops, seminars and study tours;
providing secretarial support to the Programme Director, course instructors and Programme Management Committee;
compiling reports and proposals for programme development and quality assurance;
handling student-related matters;
maintaining and updating website; and
performing any other duties as assigned.
Requirements:

a bachelor’s degree preferably with three to four years of relevant work experience;
an excellent command of English and Chinese (both Cantonese and Putonghua);
proficiency in MS Office, Chinese and English word processing, multimedia, and software for website maintenance;
good interpersonal skills and be a good team player; and
self-motivated and able to work independently.
Initial appointment will be offered on a fixed-term contract of one to two years commencing as soon as possible. Re-appointment thereafter will be subject to mutual agreement. Candidates with less experience will be considered as Executive Assistant.

Rank and salary will be commensurate with qualifications and experience.

Application Procedure:

Applicants are invited to submit their applications at the HKBU e-Recruitment System (jobs.hkbu.edu.hk). Those not invited for interview 8 weeks after the closing date may consider their applications unsuccessful. Details of the University’s Personal Information Collection Statement can be found at  http://hro.hkbu.edu.hk/pics.

The University reserves the right not to make an appointment for the post advertised, and the appointment will be made according to the terms and conditions then applicable at the time of offer.

Closing date: 26 January 2022

Job Description

Provide all-rounded secretarial support and administrative duties to the department, including but not limited to managing schedules, meeting arrangements and business travel applications and reimbursement processes etc.;
Assist in internal reports drafting, processing and internal reporting materials preparation;
Act as the point of contact among internal teams and other departments for administrative support;
Coordinate with the team in team building activities preparation, organization and execution;
Handle any ad-hoc duties as assigned.

Requirements

Bachelor degree in finance, business administration or related disciplines;
At least 2 years’ relevant experience in sizable financial institutions;
Knowledge in a wide range of investment banking products;
Detail-minded, self-motivated and is a good team player;
Proficient in written and spoken English and Chinese (including Mandarin).

We offer competitive remuneration package and comprehensive fringe benefit to the right candidate. Interested parties please forward your full resume with availability, expected salary by pressing "Apply now".

Personal data collected will be used for recruitment related purposes only. Applicants not invited for an interview within 2 months from the date of this posting may consider their applications unsuccessful. Personal data will be destroyed after 3 months.

For further information about our Company, please visit our website: https://www.cmbi.com.hk/en-US/

Duties
Reporting to the Associate Director (Student Life and Resources), the appointee will be responsible for:


Planning and organizing student development programmes, activities and special projects to support and enhance student learning;
Providing advice, support and training to Students’ Union, student societies and student groups;
Serving as the Secretary for Student Orientation Working Group, coordinating the welcoming ceremony, orientation activities for new students, and the Student Orientation website;
Coordinating the IT projects and providing support for SLR websites and social media;
Liaising with different stakeholders for student development activities/programmes; and
Performing any other duties as assigned.
The appointee will be also required to work flexible hours on a need basis.
Requirements
A Bachelor’s degree or an equivalent qualification, preferably with a postgraduate qualification;
Relevant working experience in related fields, preferably in higher education or youth work;
Working knowledge of computer applications;
Outgoing personality and ability to communicate with young people;
Good problem solving skills, being resourceful and self-motivated; and
Good command of written and spoken English and Chinese (including Putonghua).

Shortlisted candidates will be invited for a written test.

(Those who have responded to the previous advertisement need not re-apply.)


Salary and Conditions of Service

Remuneration package will be highly competitive, commensurate with qualifications and experience.  Appointment will be made on a fixed-term contract; fringe benefits include gratuity, leave, medical and dental schemes.
Information and Application
Further information on the post and the University is available at http://www.cityu.edu.hk, or from the Human Resources Office, City University of Hong Kong, Tat Chee Avenue, Kowloon Tong, Hong Kong [Fax : 2788 1154 or 3442 0311]. 

To apply, please submit an online application at http://jobs.cityu.edu.hk. The closing date is 28 January 2022.  Applications will receive full consideration and only shortlisted applicants will be contacted.  The University’s privacy policy is available on the homepage.

City University of Hong Kong is an equal opportunity employer. We are committed to the principle of diversity. Personal data provided by applicants will be used for recruitment and other employment-related purposes.

Worldwide recognition ranking #53 (QS survey 2022), and #4 among top 50 universities under age 50 (QS survey 2021); #1 in the World’s Most International Universities (THE survey 2020); #1 in Engineering/Technology/Computer Sciences in Hong Kong (ARWU survey 2016); and #1 Business School in Asia-Pacific region (UT Dallas survey 2019).

Duties: The appointee will provide administrative and secretarial support to the Secretary General and Directors as assigned. Major duties including drafting and editing documents, office administration, scheduling meetings, assisting in the preparation, compilation and distribution of Council/Committee papers and documents, maintaining filing system and publications, coordinating with internal and external parties in connection with committee work and the Authority matters, and supporting in other organisational initiatives/corporate events and projects as assigned.
Requirements:
(a)    A Bachelor’s Degree in Business Administration or related disciplines;
(b)    At least 5 years’ relevant experience in executive secretarial and/or administrative support;
(c)    Good command of spoken and written English and Chinese, knowledge of Putonghua is an advantage;
(d)    Proficient in computer applications including MS Word, Excel, Access and Chinese word processing;
(e)    Able to work independently with excellent interpersonal and communication skills;
(f)    Strong time management and organising skills;
(g)    Vigilance and attentive to details; and
(h)    Multi-tasking and able to work under pressure.
Candidates with less experience will be considered for the position of Personal Assistant.
Employment Terms:  The remuneration package will be commensurate with qualifications and experience.  Appointment will be on a fixed-term contract with contract-end-gratuity, MPF benefits, medical and dental care.  Future employment may be offered on renewable contracts subject to performance and staffing needs.
Date for Application Review: 25 January 2022
Applications would be considered until the post is filled.
Application forms can be obtained from the HKEAA office on 13/F., Southorn Centre, 130 Hennessy Road, Wan Chai, Hong Kong or downloaded from the HKEAA website (www.hkeaa.edu.hk/tc/Career/general.html).  Completed application forms should be returned to the Manager – Human Resources at the above address. Due to the secrecy nature of HKEAA's job duties, applicants invited for interview may be required to make a declaration of any conflict of interests. Applicants not notified within 10 weeks from the application review date should consider their applications unsuccessful.
The HKEAA is an equal opportunities employer and welcomes applications from all qualified candidates. Information provided relating to employment will be kept confidential and used only for processing applications. For details, please refer to the Policy Statement on Equal Opportunities and the Personal Information Collection Statement on the HKEAA website (www.hkeaa.edu.hk).

Job Duties:

The scope of your job responsibilities will include but is not limited to the following:

Comprehend petty cash management and efficiency analysis to ensure proper cashflow statements;
Maintain and monitor procurement and supply management in relation to current suppliers, credit term maintenance, and marginal cost evaluations;
Assist in sourcing items as they relate to all functions of the restaurants including but not limited to food, drink, structural, and miscellaneous goods;
Assistant accounting and human resource divisions with Owlsome group as needed at the instruction and guidance of the general manager;
Fulfil roster and shift duties across multiple restaurants as needed as the instruction and guidance of the general manager;
Assist in coordination of activities and guidelines set out by the general manager in relation to marketing, community, or group related activities as it relates to any or all of our restaurant locations;
Work hand in hand with shop managers in the daily operations of the business to help provide timely information, proper maintenance, and effective leadership as outlined and instructed by the General Manager of Owlsome restaurants;
In addition to the duties which this job normally entails, you may from time to time be required to undertake additional or other duties as necessary to meet the needs of the Company’s business;
Actively participate and support outside office company-held events occasionally;
Any company events activities as required.
Interested candidates please send full resume with expected salary by clicking “Apply Now”.


Our company is an equal opportunity employer. It provides equal opportunity to all employees and applicants for employment in accordance with all applicable laws and regulations.

Personal data collected will be treated in the strictest confidence and only be used for recruitment related purpose.
